President Obama has nominated Judge Timothy S. Hillman, Judge Robin S. Rosenbaum, and Robert J. Shelby to serve on the United States District Court bench. Judge Hillman has been a United States Magistrate Judge for the District of Massachusetts since 2006, previously serving as a Justice on the Massachusetts Superior Court and Massachusetts District Court. Judge Rosenbaum is currently a United States Magistrate Judge for the Southern District of Florida, previously working as an Assistant United States Attorney and a litigation associate at Holland & Knight. Robert J. Shelby is a shareholder at the law firm Snow, Christensen & Martineau, focusing on complex commercial litigation and catastrophic personal injury cases. He has also served as a law clerk to the Honorable J. Thomas Greene in the United States District Court for the District of Utah.